  <summary date="2023-03-15T14:27:57Z" status="Introduced in House">American Opportunity Accounts Act

This bill establishes tax-exempt American Opportunity Accounts to provide children at birth with a $1,000 savings account with annual contributions up to $2,000 depending on family income. The accounts are available to children at age 18 for specified purposes, including educational expenses, home ownership, and investment that provides long-term returns.</summary>
